title: Who Shot Ya? Deck
description: ♠ THE 1998 DECK PLAYING CARDS WILL TAKE YOUR BBQ TO THE NEXT LEVEL! Imagine playing spades with your cousin who STILL brings up that time you wet the bed. In the moment you cut his Ace of Hearts with Methodman and Redman, the universe will right itself. Imagine Playing poker with your next door neighbor and your Straight Flush ‘kicks in the door waving the four four” with Biggie & Lil Kim (I don’t know about you, but total annihilation is always a little more gully with Bad Boy “Take That, TakeThat!” ♥ THIS DECK IS ABOUT RIVALRY + 90s HIP HOP. What better way to accent the ‘war’ that sets in during a heated Spades or Poker game then by pairing it with some of the biggest contemporary ‘wars’ in Popular Culture: East Coast vs West Coast / Marcy Projects vs Queensbridge / Hardcore vs Ill Nana . The original series of The 1998 Deck pays homage not only to the 1990s, but also to the artistry and the passion of the culture: “Ether”, “Takeover”, “Who Shot Ya?” sound familiar? Well they should. Those names are borrowed from some of the most powerful diss tracks of the 1990s. ♦ YOU ARE BUYING DIRECTLY FROM THE ARTIST: Hi, my name is Khia Jackson. Whether you buy or not I am honored that you are taking the time to look at my project. I have done everything from design and delivery all on my own. I have recently taken advantage of Amazon’s amazing platform to get a farther reach. The 1998 Deck has been a labor of love. If you are a real hip hop aficionado you will recognize details in the artwork that are meant complement the artist’s personality. From Lil Kim’s Killer Bees to Andre 3000s blonde Viking wig and Busta Rhymes Love of the movie ‘Coming to America’ I borrowed from a wide inspiration. When you cop a deck, please know you are buying a true labor of love and passion. Thank you!
